      • createProfile

        private Profile createProfile​(java.lang.String input,
                              java.util.StringTokenizer st,
                              boolean open)
        Creates a Profile object with the information provided.
        Parameters:
        input - The input string containing information about the Profile.
        st - The StringTokenizer we use to parse the input string.
        open - Boolean for whether the Profile is being used for opening or closing an account.
        Returns:
        The resulting profile or null if the data in the input string would result in an invalid profile.

      • close

        private void close​(java.lang.String com)

        Parameters:
        com - The input string containing information about the account to be closed.

      • processTransaction

        private boolean processTransaction​(double amount,
                                   Profile holder,
                                   java.lang.String type,
                                   boolean deposit)
        Makes sure the transaction is valid and either deposits or withdraws from an account.
        Parameters:
        amount - The amount to deposit/withdraw.
        holder - The holder of the account as a Profile class.
        type - The type of account as a String.
        deposit - true if transaction is a deposit and false if it is a withdrawal.
        Returns:
        true if the deposit/withdrawal was successful, false if not.

      • deposit
